// Test: Module isolation - module functions CANNOT see main variables

<# ./isolated_module <= isolated

>> "=== Testing Module Isolation ===" ¶
¶

>> "--- Main program variable ---" ¶
main_variable = "I am in main program"
>> "Main variable: " main_variable ¶
¶

>> "--- Calling module function (should NOT see main_variable) ---" ¶
result = isolated::try_access_main_var("test data")
>> "Result: " result ¶
¶

>> "--- Module function with local variable ---" ¶
result2 = isolated::safe_function(10)
>> "Result: " result2 ¶
¶

>> "--- Verify main_variable still exists in main ---" ¶
>> "Main variable: " main_variable ¶
¶

>> "=== Isolation test passed! ===" ¶
>> "Module functions correctly isolated from main program" ¶
